dance_style: cha cha, cha cha cha, salsa
description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

dance_style: cha cha, cha cha cha, salsa
description: Class Description This class is dancers that have completed the Fundamentals course and want to continue to improve their social dancing using the techniques they have learned. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 9:00- 10:00pm No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Must have completed Fundamentals or have instructor permission to attend. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 4 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

dance_style: salsa, bachata, kizomba, merengue, cha cha cha
description: Bachata & Merengue are both dances from the Dominican Republic. Bachata can be anywhere from slow and romantic with lots of dips, sway and body movement to more upbeat and percussive with lots of musical footwork. Merengue is carefree, flirtatious and fun! Every Thursday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. At this time, due to COVID, all classes and rehearsals will follow personal protection rules. * Masks will be optional, and we ask that you please sanitize your hands upon arrival at the studio. * If you choose to wear a mask, please ensure that you are physically able to participate with the reduction to airflow that a mask will cause and consult an expert if necessary. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. * Experiencing symptoms? Please stay home and get better! No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: Studio 4 Athletics, 715 Yates St, Victoria, BC V8W 1L6, Canada

Bachata can be anywhere from slow and romantic with lots of dips, sway and body movement to more upbeat and percussive with lots of musical footwork. Merengue is carefree, flirtatious and fun! Every Thursday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. At this time, due to COVID, all classes and rehearsals will follow personal protection rules. * Masks will be optional, and we ask that you please sanitize your hands upon arrival at the studio. * If you choose to wear a mask, please ensure that you are physically able to participate with the reduction to airflow that a mask will cause and consult an expert if necessary. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. * Experiencing symptoms? Please stay home and get better! No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: Studio 4 Athletics, 715 Yates St, Victoria, BC V8W 1L6, Canada

dance_style: salsa, bachata, kizomba, merengue, cha cha cha
description:
Rehearsal for our Ladies Team. Open to team members by audition only. Team Description
Auditioned performance groups with rehearsals twice a week plus additional class and social requirements. The group has performed locally as well as in Puerto Rico, New York, Atlanta, Seattle and Chicago. By audition only. Open to team members by audition only. Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.

dance_style: salsa, bachata, kizomba, merengue, cha cha cha
description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

source: WCS Lessons, Social Dances, and Conventions – BC Swing Dance ...
location: Confederation Centre in North Burnaby

dance_style: salsa, bachata, kizomba, merengue, cha cha cha
description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: Studio 4 Athletics, 715 Yates St, Victoria, BC V8W 1L6, Canada

NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 9:00- 10:00pm No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Must have completed Fundamentals or have instructor permission to attend. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: Studio 4 Athletics, 715 Yates St, Victoria, BC V8W 1L6, Canada

description: Class Description This class is dancers that have completed the Fundamentals course and want to continue to improve their social dancing using the techniques they have learned. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 9:00- 10:00pm No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Must have completed Fundamentals or have instructor permission to attend. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: Studio 4 Athletics, 715 Yates St, Victoria, BC V8W 1L6, Canada

event_name: Salsa On 2 & Cha Cha Cha - Intermediate/ Advanced
dance_style: salsa, bachata, kizomba, merengue, cha cha cha

Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

dance_style: salsa, bachata, kizomba, merengue, cha cha cha
description:
Rehearsal for our Touring & Training Team. Open to team members by audition only. Team Description
Auditioned performance group with rehearsals twice a week plus additional class and social requirements. The group has performed locally as well as in Puerto Rico, New York, Italy, Atlanta, Seattle, Chicago and on the All-Star Cruise. By audition only. Open to team members by audition only. No partner required. Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.
location: Studio 4 Athletics, 715 Yates St, Victoria, BC V8W 1L6, Canada

dance_style: salsa, bachata, kizomba, merengue, cha cha cha
description:
Rehearsal for our Student Bachata Team. Open to team members only. Team Description
Local all levels performance group with rehearsals once a week. If you have never performed before or have a limited amount of time you are able to commit to, this is the team for you. Learn exciting choreographies to perform at local events with no pressure to perform until you are ready. Open to team members only. No dance experience, partner or audition required! Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.
location: Studio 4 Athletics, 715 Yates St, Victoria, BC V8W 1L6, Canada

description: Dancing the 4th Friday of every month at an all ages venue right in the heart of downtown, with a wooden dance floor. 7:45pm Doors open, 8:00pm Salsa lesson, 9:00pm- midnight Dancing to Salsa, Bachata, Merengue, Cha Cha Cha and more. All ages welcome. Limited capacity. First come first served. We reserve the right to refuse entrance at the door.
location: Dance City, downtown
price: $15.00 per person + service fee on Eventbrite or cash only at the door. $13 cash for Edelweiss Club members at the door only.

description: We are excited to bring you dancing the 4th Friday of every month at an all ages venue right in the heart of downtown, with a wooden dance floor!!!!! 7:45pm Doors open Salsa Caliente’s team will be there to greet you. 8:00pm Salsa lesson Taught by World Salsa University certified instructor, Christina Morrison. No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson so you will already know a LOT of people by the time the dancing begins. 9:00pm- midnight Dancing to Salsa, Bachata, Merengue, Cha Cha Cha and more. All ages welcome. $15.00 per person + service fee on Eventbrite or cash only at the door. $13 cash for Edelweiss Club members at the door only. *Limited capacity. First come first served. We reserve the right to refuse entrance at the door.
location: Victoria Edelweiss Club, 108 Niagara St, Victoria, BC V8V 1E9, Canada

event_name: Bar Stage In the Mood Quintet featuring Angela Verbrugge
dance_style: swing, jive, foxtrot, cha-cha-cha, salsa, waltz, quickstep, tango
description: Come to early set at the Coda at 751 View/Blanshard on Friday, March 7 to enjoy a cocktail, vocal jazz, and a swing dance. The evening will led by the vocalist nominated for Western Canadian Music Awards’ 2024 Jazz Artist of the Year and who recently won the All About Jazz poll for Fav Living Jazz Vocalist. Don your cutest vintage attire, hat, or jewelry, and order an old-fashioned for retro vintage fun. A variety of favourite jazz standards, swing era hits, and grooves will be covered by this A+ quintet including swing, jive, foxtrot, cha-cha-cha, salsa, waltz, quickstep, and tango… or just sit back and watch.
source: The Coda: Friday Speakeasy Vibes, Vocal Jazz and Swing Dance ...
location: Coda at 751 View/Blanshard
price: $20 General Admission - + Price at door: $25 Optional donation for the band

description: Celebrate St. Patrick’s Day with us on Sunday, March 30th, 2025, for an evening of Latin social dancing with our St. Patrick’s theme! 🍀 As we embrace the spirit of St. Patrick’s Day, come dressed in green and you’ll be entered into a raffle for a chance to win a special prize. 🕓 Event Schedule: Doors Open: 4:15 PM Beginner Bachata Lesson with Ghada: 4:30 PM - 5:00 PM The dance style varies each month. Social Dancing: 5:00 PM - 8:30 PM Join us in James Bay at 111 Superior Street, where we’ll be heating things up with Salsa, Bachata, Kizomba, and Merengue.

event_name: Emerald City March Social Dance - Members
description: Join us for an evening of fun and dancing at our March 15th “Emerald City” themed social dance! Wanda will start the evening off with a “Hesitation Waltz” mixer workshop at 7:00 p.m., followed by general dancing from 7:45 to 9:45 p.m. If you want to join in on the theme and walk down “the yellow brick road” to Emerald City with us – think green and money! Light refreshments will be served.
location: Les Passmore (Silver Threads), 286 Hampton Road

event_name: May Sweet Send-Off Social Dance - Members
description: It’s time to say “Goodbye” to the season with a Sweet Send-off that’s sure to leave you smiling and dancing all night long! Whether you’re bringing your sweetheart or flying solo, we’ve got a night packed with sweet treats, dance floor fun, and plenty of memorable moments! The evening will feature special Class Demos, showcasing the fantastic moves from our talented dancers, followed by a Team Match that will keep you on your toes! The music will keep us grooving until 9:45 p.m., with plenty of general dancing in between. So, don’t forget to grab your sweetie for a photo moment and snap a pic to remember the night by! So grab your sweetie, lace up those sweet dance shoes, and come on over for a few hours of fun and dancing! We can’t wait to sweeten your Saturday night! Secure your spot now and bring your dance-loving friends!
location: Les Passmore – Silver Threads, 286 Hampton Road

location: Dance Victoria at 2750 Quadra Street , just north of Hillside.

event_name: April Spring Garden Party Social Dance - Members
description: Step into spring with a night full of blooms, beats, and beautiful moments! Our Spring Garden Party is just around the corner, and we’re inviting YOU to join us for a night of music, fun, and dancing under a canopy of colorful flowers. Tango, Treats & a Dash of Spring Magic! We’ll kick things off with a lively tango workshop by the fabulous Gaetan Rouette at 7:00 p.m. From there, we’ll keep the dance floor warm with general dancing until 9:45 p.m. Between your spins and twirls, be sure to snap a pic at our vibrant, spring-themed photo booth, and enjoy the delicious, seasonal treats we’ll have waiting for you! Let the Spring Blooms inspire your every step as we celebrate the fresh, energetic vibes of the season. Special Mixer: Jack & Jill! Join in our fun social mixer and team up for a chance to win amazing prizes! Grab a dance partner as we shuffle and sway through this unique, interactive dance game. Don’t forget to wear your dancing shoes and a touch of spring in your outfit – it’s going to be a blooming good time! Secure your spot now and dance into the heart of spring with us!
location: Les Passmore – Silver Threads, 286 Hampton Road
